description.narrative: 106/001 Governments and partners have increased capacity to provide continued access to Health services and critical supplies for women and children for strengthening Infection Prevention and Control and for suppressing the COVID-19 transmission at community level, which contributes to Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Maternal And Newborn Health (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 6. By 2022, children and women have equitable access to knowledge and services related to COVID-19 prevention and treatment in the areas of health, nutrition, education, WASH and child protection in the most deprived areas, including Rohingya refugee camps.
